menu "App Config"

config DEV_MODE
    bool "Enable developer mode"
    default y
    help
      When enabled, the firmware will keep the web server running even after
      Wi-Fi is configured, and may enable other dev-only features.

config SENTINEL_ENABLE_OFF_SLEEP_GATE
    bool "Pause periodic monitoring and enter WoM light sleep when patrol RMS is low"
    default y
    help
      When enabled, patrol RMS below the configured threshold for several
      consecutive patrol windows will pause periodic monitoring, arm LIS2DH12
      WoM wakeup, and enter light sleep until motion wakes the device.

config SENTINEL_OFF_RMS_THRESHOLD_MM_S
    int "Patrol RMS threshold for OFF gating (mm/s)"
    range 0 100
    default 1
    depends on SENTINEL_ENABLE_OFF_SLEEP_GATE
    help
      If the maximum RMS across X/Y/Z during patrol is below this value, the
      sample is considered a low-energy OFF candidate.

config SENTINEL_OFF_CONFIRM_COUNT
    int "Consecutive low-RMS patrol windows required before sleep"
    range 1 10
    default 2
    depends on SENTINEL_ENABLE_OFF_SLEEP_GATE
    help
      Number of consecutive patrol RMS windows below threshold required before
      periodic tasks are paused and the device enters WoM light sleep.

config SENTINEL_BOOT_AP_CONNECT_WINDOW_SEC
    int "Boot AP connect window (seconds)"
    range 1 300
    default 10
    help
      Time window after boot during which the device waits for a client to
      connect to the configuration AP before continuing into the main program.

config SENTINEL_BOOT_AP_CONFIG_WINDOW_SEC
    int "Boot AP configuration window after client connect (seconds)"
    range 1 600
    default 60
    help
      If a client connects to the configuration AP during boot, the device
      waits this long for configuration submission before continuing into the
      main program automatically.

endmenu
